ActIndian Act
SubjectAddition to Alderville First Nation Indian Reserve, in Ontario
PrecisOrder setting apart 31.78 hectares (78.53 acres) of lands, including mines and minerals, for the use and benefit of Alderville First Nation as an addition to ALDERVILLE FIRST NATION INDIAN RESERVE, located in the County of Northumberland in the geographic Township of Alnwick approximately 22 kilometres from the county of Peterborough, Ontario.
